    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Park Rampage: Women as Targets</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Harry J Byrne letter on June 17 article cites television programs that give aura of acceptability to stripping of women and personal violence as factors in Central Park rampage</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your June 17 front-page article describes a volatile mixture of weather, testosterone and police lapses exploding into the rampage against women in Central Park after the June 11 National Puerto Rican Day Parade. Might there not also be some connection between this stripping of women and personal violence with the aura of acceptability given such phenomena in TV shows and videos with the complicity of entertainment executives?</p>
        <p>HARRY J. BYRNE  New York, June 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
